Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Core, deseed, and dice @Bell Pepper{1} into ½-inch pieces. Toss potatoes on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{}, @Smoked Paprika{1/2%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Toss bell pepper on empty side with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper. Roast on top rack until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> TIP: If needed, divide between 2 sheets; roast potatoes on top rack and peppers on middle rack.

While veggies roast, heat a large pan over medium-high heat. Add @Bacon{4%ounce} and cook, turning occasionally, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. 

> TIP: Adjust heat if bacon begins to brown too quickly.

Turn off heat and transfer to a #cutting board{}. Drain all but a thin layer of bacon fat from pan. Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop half the bacon.

While bacon cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine @Ketchup{2%tablespoon} and remaining @Smoked Paprika{1/2%teaspoon}. In a separate small bowl, combine @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon}, a big pinch of @salt{}, and as much @Hot Sauce{2%teaspoon} as you like; stir in @water{1%teaspoon} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. In a #large bowl{}, combine @Ground Beef{10%ounce}, scallion whites, @salt{3/4%teaspoon}, and pepper. Form mixture into two patties, each slightly wider than a burger bun. Heat pan with reserved bacon fat over medium-high heat. Add patties; cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

> We used 3/4 tsp kosher salt; 1 1/2 tsp for 4 servings.

Meanwhile, halve @Brioche Buns{2}. Place cut sides up on a second baking sheet; top bottom buns with @Gouda Cheese{2%slice}. Toast on middle rack until buns are golden and cheese has melted, ~{3-5%minutes}. While buns toast, heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for patties over medium heat. Once hot, crack @Eggs{2} into pan and cover. Fry eggs to preference. Uncover and season with salt and pepper.

Fill buns with patties, smoky ketchup, hot sauce crema (save a bit of each for the hash), bacon slices, and eggs. Toss together veggies, then divide between plates with burgers. Top veggie hash with chopped bacon and scallion greens, then drizzle with remaining ketchup and crema. Serve.